<p>Pralay is expected to have&nbsp;large-scale action with strong human emotions, revolving around a family in distress. Being made on Rs 300 crore budget, approx, the film marks the most expensive standalone project of Ranveer&rsquo;s career. While <a href="https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/exclusives/exclusive-yami-gautam-set-to-make-a-cameo-in-aditya-dhars-dhurandhar-2-with-ranveer-singh-1400426">Dhurandhar</a> was mounted on a larger scale, its two-part format split the production costs, making Pralay his biggest single-film investment to date.</p>

<p>A source close to the development reveals, &ldquo;Ranveer has entered into a backend profit-sharing deal and is involved in every stage, from script development to VFX planning. This is also the maiden venture under his production banner, Maa Kasam Films, making it even more special for him.&rdquo;</p>

