<p><strong>New Tune Calling!!</strong></p>

<p>But this isn&rsquo;t a goodbye, folks; it&rsquo;s a hello to a new chapter in his life: filmmaking.</p>

<p>He cited a desire to explore new creative horizons as the reason behind his retirement from singing. While <a href="https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/arijit-singh-announces-retirement-from-playback-singing-i-am-calling-it-off-it-was-a-wonderful-journey-1400254">Arijit Singh</a>&rsquo;s decision to quit singing may have come as a shock, it isn&rsquo;t entirely unexpected. A perfectionist at heart, he has always been driven by the urge to explore and create. Knowing his passion, he now wants to focus on direction and production.</p>

<p>His debut Hindi film will feature Nawazuddin Siddiqui&rsquo;s daughter, Shora, and Arijit&rsquo;s son in lead roles. The jungle adventure film is co-produced by Arijit and his wife, Koel Singh, along with Mahavir Jain.</p>

<p>The film&rsquo;s schedule is currently underway in Shantiniketan, with <a href="https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/exclusives/exclusive-nawazuddin-siddiqui-opens-up-on-his-struggle-days-says-he-has-no-complaints-about-life-1321775">Nawazuddin Siddiqui</a> making a special appearance. Veteran actor Dibyendu Bhattacharya is also part of the cast. Arijit&rsquo;s wife, Koel Singh, has co-written the script with him, and the duo is excited to bring their story to life. According to sources, before its pan-India release, the film will be screened at several film festivals.</p>

<p>This isn&rsquo;t Arijit&rsquo;s first foray into filmmaking. He previously directed a Bengali film, Sa (2018), which revolved around a young boy&rsquo;s musical journey.</p>

<p>As Arijit Singh embarks on this new path, fans and the industry alike are eager to see what he brings to the table. With his passion and dedication, we&rsquo;re sure to witness something truly special. The curtain may have fallen on his playback singing career, but&nbsp;the show is far from over. Arijit will definately continue with his singles and concerts as his own pace.</p>

<p>Here&rsquo;s to the maestro&rsquo;s next big hit&mdash;on celluloid! As we know&hellip; Picture Abhi Baaki Hai.</p>
